  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Structural Designer",
  "description": "<p><u><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></u><br /><u><strong></strong></u></p><ul><li>Create accurate 3D models and production-level 2D drawings of offshore structures and general arrangement drawings using professional 3D modeling tools (E3D, PDMS, or similar) and 2D AutoCAD software</li><li>Produce detailed drawings including beams, brackets, welds, flanges, bolted connections, and materials take-off for fabrication of offshore assemblies</li><li>Prepare technical documentation and support construction teams with detailed fabrication drawings, weight calculations, and bill of materials</li><li>Prepare material take-offs, weight estimates, and maintain technical drawings through project lifecycles</li><li>Interface with engineers, and fabrication teams, ensuring alignment throughout all design stages</li><li>Understanding of structural steel detailing, Classification Rules and basic offshore engineering principles</li></ul><p><u><strong>Requirements:</strong></u><br /></p><ul><li>Diploma in Civil or Structural Engineering.</li><li>A minimum of 5 years’ (up to 8 years’) working experience as Structural Designer in Offshore Oil & Gas fabrication.</li><li>Knowledge in the use of Aveva E3D Structural Modelling.</li><li>Well-versed in Navisworks.</li></ul>",
